# Defence-in-depth: a decoded copy of the git-crypt symmetric key must
# never land in a commit. The real key lives in 1Password (base64) and
# is loaded into `.git/git-crypt/keys/default` (untracked) by
# `scripts/setup`.
*.gitcrypt-key
gitcrypt.key
gitcrypt.key.bin

# Phase 20 — per-fixture state files written by `aflare-e2e provision`.
# Resource IDs are deterministic per <sha7>, so concurrent runs on
# different SHAs don't collide; the local file just lets `teardown` /
# `list` skip a round-trip to the Cloudflare API.
tests/e2e/.state/
